'''天宫三号'''是[[中國空間站|中國空間站]]计划中的一个已取消的[[空间实验室|空间实验室]]，同时也是[[中华人民共和国|中国]]原定“[[载人航天|载人航天]]三步走”计划中第二步的收官任务。中国载人航天工程办公室原计划将在2015年左右发射天宫三号。<ref name="sdc20110307">{{cite news|last=David|first=Leonard|title=China Details Ambitious Space Station Goals|url=http://www.space.com/11048-china-space-station-plans-details.html|access-date=2011-03-09|newspaper=Space.com|date=2011-03-11|quote=China is ready to carry out a multiphase construction program that leads to the large space station around 2020. As a prelude to building that facility, China is set to loft the Tiangong-1 module this year as a platform to help master key rendezvous and docking technologies.|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320030556/http://www.space.com/11048-china-space-station-plans-details.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>但随后计划改变，天宫三号任务被取消，其原定[[科学实验|科研实验]]项目分别由[[天宫二号|天宫二号]]和[[天和号核心舱|天和号核心舱]]完成。<ref>{{cite web|title=脚踏实地，仰望星空—访中国载人航天工程总设计师周建平|url=http://www.cmse.gov.cn/art/2016/4/28/art_18_27619.html|publisher=Chinese Government|access-date=2017-04-22|archive-date=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009120137/http://www.cmse.gov.cn/art/2016/4/28/art_18_27619.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="china201711">{{cite web|url=http://www.china.com.cn/news/2017-11/22/content_41929256.htm|date=2017-11-22|title="天宫二号"总设计师：不再有天宫三号 五年后建成空间站|quote=“天宫二号”后，不再开发“天宫三号”，中国将直接进入空间站时代，空间站预计2022年建成|access-date=2021-04-30|archive-date=2021-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210430111214/http://www.china.com.cn/news/2017-11/22/content_41929256.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 概要 ==
2008年，[[中國載人航天工程辦公室|中国载人航天工程办公室]]透露了一部分有关“[[天宫二号|天宫二号]]”和“天宫三号”的简要信息，表示将在2010年代末发射一系列载人飞船与“天宫三号”进行对接。<ref>{{cite web|title=future plan of space laboratory system (in Chinese)|url=http://www.cmse.gov.cn/cha_xtzc/show.php?itemid=120|date=2008-09-29|dead-url=yes|archive-url=https://archive.is/20080928025107/http://www.cmse.gov.cn/cha_xtzc/show.php?itemid=120|archive-date=2008-09-28|access-date=2021-02-19}}</ref>

天宫三号原计划将会验证再生生保关键技术、[[航天员|航天员]]中期在轨驻留、[[航天器|飞行器]]长期在轨自主飞行和[[貨運飛船|货运飞船]]在轨试验等一系列[[空间站|空间站]]关键技术，并将开展部分[[空间科学|空间科学]]和航天医学试验。后为节省[[經費|经费]]并加快[[中国空间站工程|中国空间站工程]]的建设步伐，加之原定用于发射天宫三号的[[长征五号B运载火箭|长征五号B运载火箭]]研制进度不如预期，天宫三号任务被取消，原定技术试验项目由天宫二号和未来的中国空间站分摊完成。

== 参数规格 ==
天宫三号由实验舱和资源舱构成，前后两个对接口，可同时对接一艘[[载人飞船|载人飞船]]和一艘[[貨運飛船|货运飞船]]，预计将重达22吨，长约18.1米，最大直径为4.2米，<ref>{{Cite web |title=我国空间站冷知识，在天和之前曾想发射天宫三号，为何最终取消？_核心_试验_飞船 |url=https://www.sohu.com/a/518147900_120399893 |website=www.sohu.com |language=en |access-date=2022-06-18}}</ref>按计划将：

* 具备3名[[航天员|航天员]]中期在轨驻留40天的能力；<ref name="sdc201103072">{{cite news|last=David|first=Leonard|title=China Details Ambitious Space Station Goals|url=http://www.space.com/11048-china-space-station-plans-details.html|access-date=2011-03-09|newspaper=Space.com|date=2011-03-11|quote=China is ready to carry out a multiphase construction program that leads to the large space station around 2020. As a prelude to building that facility, China is set to loft the Tiangong-1 module this year as a platform to help master key rendezvous and docking technologies.|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320030556/http://www.space.com/11048-china-space-station-plans-details.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* 再生循环式[[生命保障系统|生命保障系统]]的关键技术试验以及[[貨運飛船|货运飞船]]在轨燃料加注技术的试验验证；<ref name="sdc201103073">{{cite news|last=David|first=Leonard|title=China Details Ambitious Space Station Goals|url=http://www.space.com/11048-china-space-station-plans-details.html|access-date=2011-03-09|newspaper=Space.com|date=2011-03-11|quote=China is ready to carry out a multiphase construction program that leads to the large space station around 2020. As a prelude to building that facility, China is set to loft the Tiangong-1 module this year as a platform to help master key rendezvous and docking technologies.|archive-date=2016-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320030556/http://www.space.com/11048-china-space-station-plans-details.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* 同时对接多个飞行器的[[航天器|航天器]]在轨停泊机制。<ref name="ukg20110426">{{cite news|title=China unveils rival to International Space Station|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/apr/26/china-space-station-tiangong|access-date=2011-04-27|newspaper=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=2011-04-26|quote=China often chooses poetic names for its space projects, such as Chang'e – after the moon goddess – for its lunar probes; its rocket series, however, is named Long March, in tribute to communist history. The space station project is currently referred to as Tiangong, or "heavenly palace".|location=London|first1=Tania|last1=Branigan|first2=Ian|last2=Sample|archive-date=2020-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223092533/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/apr/26/china-space-station-tiangong|dead-url=no}}</ref>

